# ==============================================================================
# 🐳 Matrix Orchestration Configuration (REMOTE / CLUSTER)
# ==============================================================================
# 📋 Purpose:
# - This file is automatically read by 'docker compose' in this directory.
# - Target: Stable Deployment / Cluster Orchestration.
# ==============================================================================

# 📦 Active Image Selection
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default: Stable Go-based engine from GHCR.
HOTPLEX_IMAGE=hotplex:go 

# 🛠️ Optional Image Registry (Tech Stacks)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# You can change HOTPLEX_IMAGE to any of the following tags:
#
# | 镜像标签 (Tag)       | 远程镜像名                         | 核心技术栈     | 适用场景                               |
# | :------------------ | :-------------------------------- | :------------ | :------------------------------------ |
# | hotplex:go          | ghcr.io/hrygo/hotplex:latest-go   | Go 1.26       | 默认。核心引擎开发、高性能扩展           |
# | hotplex:node        | ghcr.io/hrygo/hotplex:latest-node | Node.js 24    | MCP 服务、前端组件、Bun 轻量工具        |
# | hotplex:python      | ghcr.io/hrygo/hotplex:latest-python | Python 3.14   | AI 算法集成、数据处理、LLM 脚本         |
# | hotplex:java        | ghcr.io/hrygo/hotplex:latest-java | JDK 25        | 企业级应用集成、Java 插件开发           |
# | hotplex:rust        | ghcr.io/hrygo/hotplex:latest-rust | Rust 1.94     | 高性能系统组件、极低延迟模块             |
# | hotplex:full        | ghcr.io/hrygo/hotplex:latest-full | 全技术栈      | 全能模式。跨语言协作、复杂调试环境       |
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 🐍 Python Tools Auto-Install (Optional)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Format: Space-separated list, supports pkg:bin format to specify binary name
# Example: "notebooklm-py:notebooklm pandas httpie"
# Tools are installed via uv on container startup
# PIP_TOOLS=notebooklm-py:notebooklm
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
